      • getPriority

        public Long getPriority()
        Optional. Gets or sets the priority of this endpoint when using the ‘Priority’ traffic routing method. Possible values are from 1 to 1000, lower values represent higher priority. This is an optional parameter. If specified, it must be specified on all endpoints, and no two endpoints can share the same priority value.
        Returns:
        The Priority value.

        Parameters:
